Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '463'. Name Aristogenes. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0072.38.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (69)
